\vdots\\
\mu_{m}
\end{bmatrix},\Sigma_{X}=\begin{bmatrix}\Sigma_{1} & 0 & 0 & 0\\
0 & \Sigma_{2} & 0 & 0\\
0 & 0 & \ddots & 0\\
0 & 0 & 0 & \Sigma_{n}
\end{bmatrix}\right).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
For any 
\begin_inset Formula $t\in\mathbb{R}^{\sum_{i=1}^{m}n_{i}}$
\end_inset

, we note that by triangularizing it follows that 
\begin_inset Formula 
